---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';

const title = "About — AI Finance Lab";
const description = "An AI engineer who got tired of bad fintech reviews. Here's why I built this site and how I evaluate AI finance tools.";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={title} description={description} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1>Hi, I'm an AI engineer who got tired of bad fintech reviews.</h1>

			<h2>My background</h2>
			<p>
				I work on large language model algorithms. I read research papers, train models,
				and benchmark AI systems for a living. When I looked at how AI finance tools are
				reviewed online, I found a pattern: screenshots of dashboards, walkthroughs of
				signup flows, and zero analysis of the actual algorithms. Nobody was asking the
				questions that matter.
			</p>

			<h2>Why this site exists</h2>
			<p>
				Most AI finance tool reviews are surface-level. They show you the UI, list the
				features from the pricing page, and call it a day. But "AI-powered" is the most
				abused label in fintech right now. Algorithm transparency, data security, and
				whether the AI is real or just a marketing wrapper — nobody tests these things
				rigorously. I do.
			</p>

			<h2>How I review</h2>
			<p>Every tool is evaluated across four dimensions:</p>
			<ol>
				<li><strong>Algorithm Transparency</strong> — Does the tool explain what model it uses? Open weights? White paper?</li>
				<li><strong>Data Security</strong> — Where does your financial data go? On-device, encrypted cloud, or sold to third parties?</li>
				<li><strong>Real AI vs Marketing</strong> — Is there a genuine model behind the product, or is it a wrapper around a public API with a nice UI?</li>
				<li><strong>Accuracy Benchmarks</strong> — I test predictions, classifications, and recommendations against real data. No cherry-picked screenshots.</li>
			</ol>

			<h2>What I'm not</h2>
			<p>
				I'm not a financial advisor. Nothing on this site is financial advice.
				All content is for informational and educational purposes only.
				Some links may be affiliate links — when they are, I disclose it in the article.
				Do your own research before making any financial decisions.
			</p>

			<p>
				<a href="/newsletter">→ Subscribe to the newsletter</a> for one deep-dive review per week.
			</p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
